==English==

====Etymology====
Middle [[English]], from middle [[French]] ''definer'', from [[Latin]] ''definire''

===Pronunciation===
{{rfap}}
'''\de-fine\''''
{{rfp}}

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|defin|e}}

# To [[determine]].
# To express the essential [[nature]] of something.
# To state of the [[meaning]] of a [[word]] or word group or a sign or symbol.
# To describe, explain, or making definite and [[clear]].
# To demark sharply the outlines or limits of an area or concept.

